# https://hub.docker.com/r/phpmyadmin/phpmyadmin/
# --link spawning-pool:db  * Phpmyadmin must point to MySQL Server. So that we must link both containers by adding the option : â€“link name-of-container:name-of-imag.
# https://omarghader.github.io/docker-tutorial-phpmyadmin-and-mysql-server/
# The option --link provides access to another container running in the host. 
# In our case the container is the one created in the previous section, called my-own-mysql and the resource accessed is the MySQL db.
